STANDARD IN (0) :
    
    REDIRECT INPUT TO COMMAND : command < Filename


STANDARD OUT (1) : 

    CREATE EMPTY FILE : > Filename

    OVERWRITE WITH REDIRECTION : echo New Message > Filename

    APPEND AT ENDING OF FILE WITH REDIRECTION : echo New Message >> Filename


STANDARD ERROR (2) : 

    REDIRECT ERROR MESSAGES TO FILE : commands 2>> Filename

    REDIRECT BOTH ERROR AND OUTPUT : commands &>> Filename

    DISCARD ALL OUTPUTS : commands &> /dev/null

    REDIRECT MESSAGES TO DESIRED ACTIVE TERMINAL : commands > /dev/pts/0


CAT : 

    READ FILES : cat file_1 file_2 file_N
    
    ADD LINE NUMBER : cat -n Filename


MORE : 

    READ FILE IN PARTED MANNER : more Filename


LESS :

    READ FILE IN PAGED MANNER : less Path/To/File

    QUIT LESS MODE : q

    SEARCH IN LESS MODE : /KeyWord

    
HEAD & TAIL : 

    SEE FIRST N LINES IN FILE : head -n N Path/To/File

    SEE LAST N LINES IN FILE : tail -n N Path/To/File

    SEE LIVE UPDATES AT ENDING OF FILE : tail -f Path/To/File


WORD LINE COUNT : 

    NUMBER OF WORDS IN FILE : wc -w Filename

    NUMBER OF LINES IN FILE : wc -l Filename

    NUMBER OF BYTES IN FILE : wc -c Filename

    ADD COUNT TO EACH LINE : nl Filename


CUT : 
    
    Nth CHARACTOR FROM EACH LINE : cut -c N Filename

    Nth PART BY FIELD SAPERATOR WITH DELIMITER : cut -f N -d "delimiter" Filename 

    WITH RANGE : 

        Nth TO Mth INDEX : cut -c N-M Filename

        START TO Nth CHARACTOR : cut -c -N Filename

        Nth CHARACTOR TO ENDING : cut -c N- Filename

        OUTPUT DELIMITER FOR MULTIPLE FIELDS : cut -c -M,A-K,P- --output-delimiter "delimiter" Filename

        
PASTE : 

    MERGE LINES IN A FILE : paste -d 'delimiter' -s Filename
    

JOIN AND SPLIT : 

    JOIN CONTENTS OF TWO SORTED FILES : join File_1 File_2

    JOIN CONTENTS OF TWO UNSORTED FILES WITH MATCHING FIELD : join -1 Nth -2 Mth File_1 File_2

    SPLIT FILE INTO FILES WITH EACH N LINES : split -l N BigFile


PIPE & TEE : 

    OUTPUT OF ONE COMMAND INPUT FOR ANOTHER : command_1 | command_2  | command_3 

    OUTPUT OF ONE PROCESS INPUT FOR MULTIPLE : command_1 | tee command_2 Filename


XARGS : 

    CONVERT STANDARD OUTPUT INTO ARGUMENT : commands_with_stdout | xargs commands_with_argument_need

    GET N WORDS PER LINE FROM A FILE OR COMMANDS OUTPUT : echo "Filename" | xargs -n N echo

    SPLIT ON NULL CHARACTOR : echo "Filename" | xargs -n N -0 echo

    REPLACEMET : 

        ADD GIVEN MESSAGE FOR EACH OUTPUT LINE : echo "Filename" | xargs -n N  -I {} echo "Message" {}

        USE EVRY WORD IN FILE AS NAME FOR NEW FILES IN GIVEN FOLDER : echo "Filename" | xargs -I {} /Path/To/Folder {}.extension

        MODIFY PERMISSIONS FOR SPECIFIC FILES : echo "Filename" | xargs -I {} chmod rwx {}


SORT : 

    SORT BY CHARACTOR VALUE : sort Filename

    SORT REVERSE BY CHARACTOR VALUE : sort -r Filename

    SORT BY NUMERIC VALUE : sort -n Filename

    SORT UNIQUE VALUES : sort -u Filename

    SORT UNIQUE VALUES CASE INSESITIVE : sort -uf Filename

    SORT BY COLUMN Nth VALUES : sort -k2 Filename


UNIQUE : 

    REMOVE DUPLICATE LINES : uniq Filename

    GET UNIQUE VALUES ONLY : uniq -u Filename

    GET DUPLICATE VALUES ONLY : uniq -d Filename

    GET DUPLICATE VALUES WITH DUPLICATES : uniq -D Filename

    OVERCOME NON ADJECENT DUPLICATES : sort Filename | uniq


TRANSLATE : 

    CONVERT LOWER CASE TO UPPER CASE : tr a-z A-Z < Filename_OR_OtherInput

    DELETE GIVEN CHARACTOR : tr -d GivenCharactorSet < Filename_OR_OtherInput

    REPLACE ONE WITH ANOTHER : tr 'OldCharactors' 'NewCharactors' < Filename


SED : 

    SUBSTITUTE OCCURENCE IN LINE : 

        FOR ALL LINES : 

            sed 's/old_Value/New_Value/g' Filename
            sed 's:old_Value:New_Value:g' Filename

        FOR SPECIFIC NTH LINE OR EXCEPT IT : 

            sed 'N s/old_Value/New_Value/g' Filename
            sed 'N! s:old_Value:New_Value:g' Filename

    MULTIPLE SED COMMANDS : sed -e 's/old/new/g' -e 's/old2/new2/g' Filename

    USE SEDFILE CONTAINING SED COMMANDS : sed -f SedFile Filename
    
    TURN OFF PRINTING : sed -n 's/old/new/g' Filename

    PRINT ONLY UPDATED LINES : sed -n 's/old/new/p' Filename

    GET ONLY NTH LINE : sed -n 'Np' Filename

    GET ONLY LAST LINE : sed -n '$p' Filename

    DELETE NTH LINE : sed 'Nd' Filename

    PRINT IN RANGE OF NtH TO Mth LINE : sed -n 'N,M p' Filename

    PRINT AFTER FINDING LINE START WITH X TILL FINDING LINE START WITH Y : sed -n '/^X,/^Y/p' Filename

    GET LINES CONTAINING KEYWORD : sed -n '/KeyWord/p' Filename

    GET N MORE LINES FROM MTH LINE : sed -n 'M,+N p' Filename
    
    GET MORE LINES FROM N WITH M LINES SKIPPED : sed -n 'N~Mp' Filename
    
    APPLY CHANGES IN FILE : sed -i 's/Old/New/g' Filename

    REPLACE AFTER FINDING KEYWORD : sed '/KeyWord/ s/Old/New/g' Filename

    DELETE EMPTY LINES : sed '/^$/d' Filename

    TRANSFER SEARCHED DATA TO OTHER FILE : sed '/KeyWord/ w NewFileName' Filename

    APPEND AFTER NTH LINE : sed 'N a Write_Something' Filename

    CHANGE NTH LINE : sed 'N c Something_Write' Filename

    INSERT IN NTH LINE : sed 'N i Something_write' Filename

    SEE HIDDEN CHARACTORS : sed -n 'l' Filename

    ADD CONTENT OF A FILE AT NTH LINE : sed 'N r FileName' FileName

    QUIT AFTER FIRST OCCURENCE : sed '/KeyWord/ q' Filename

    ADD EXPRESSION AT NTH LINE : sed 'N e Commands' Filename

    PRINT LINE NUMBER : sed '=' Filename

